<%- include('partials/header') %>
<main class="container">
  <div class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Backup</p>
    <h1>Link map export &amp; import</h1>
    <p class="lead">A portable record of every page/section/variant and every short link's
      current file — the thing worth never losing, since these URLs get embedded all over
      once published. Excludes users, sessions, and storage credentials.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Export</h2>
    <p class="muted small">Downloads a JSON snapshot of the taxonomy + link/slug map (including
      redirect history for renamed slugs). Small, text-diffable, safe to commit to git.</p>
    <a class="btn primary" href="/api/admin/export" download>Export link map (.json)</a>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Import</h2>
    <p class="muted small">Restores from an exported file. <strong>Never overwrites</strong> a
      slug or taxonomy entry that already exists — only adds what's missing, so it's safe to
      run against a live database. Note: this restores the <em>map</em>, not file bytes — for
      local storage, the actual files must already be present (e.g. from <code>data/uploads/</code>
      in git); for Bunny/S3, the bytes are wherever they were originally uploaded.</p>
    <div class="row wrap">
      <input type="file" id="importFile" accept="application/json" />
      <button class="btn primary" id="importBtn">Import</button>
    </div>
    <div id="importMsg" class="msg"></div>
    <div id="importSummary" class="hidden"></div>
  </section>
</main>
<script src="/public/admin-backup.js"></script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
